this is the doc file for the flask

commands to create an environment
mkdir Project_name(myproject)
cd myproject
py -3 -m venv Virtual_environment_name(venv)


Activate the environment
Virtual_environment_name(venv)\Scripts\Activate
if it is not working change the access policy rules
https://superuser.com/questions/106360/how-to-enable-execution-of-powershell-scripts


intall the flask 
pip install flask


A minimal Application

from flask import flask
app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def hello_world():
    return 'Hello, World!'

Note:Do not save the file with name "flask.py" and save it with app.py

and then run python -m flask run


